summary: Bill Fanter provides a comprehensive weekly watchlist for December 8th week, emphasizing the critical FOMC rate decision on Wednesday and advising traders to sit out due to inflated options premiums. He conducts detailed technical analysis on major indices (SPY, QQQ) and individual stocks (AAPL, GOOGL, TSLA, META, NVDA, AMD, PLTR) using fibonacci retracements, gap fills, and supply/demand zones. The analysis highlights relative strength in select names while noting market broadening beyond Mag 7 stocks, with specific entry levels and directional bias for multiple trading opportunities.
